data.message:
re-architect: separate Constraint and IK functions

The original design required users to sub-class an existing constrained_ik (or derivative) class to add new constraints.  This design imposed a serial ordering on constraint implementations.  There was no easy way to "mix-and-match" constraints if you wanted to ignore/disable one of the intermediate constraints.  This re-design implements constraints as standalone classes, and users may select which combination of constraints to use.
  - create new Constraint and ConstraintGroup classes
  - push content of old Basic_IK class into new Constraint::GoalPosition and Constraint::GoalOrientation classes.
  - modify Basic_IK to instantiate a default set of Constraints, where the actual "work" is done
